{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-unspsc-43"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Independent IT Asset Recovery & E-Waste Refurbishment Robotics"
 :itonami.blueprint/unspsc-segment "43"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :circular/it-asset-disposition
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:e-waste-reduction :data-safety :digital-access-affordability]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :it-asset-recovery-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :telemetry :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "TriageAdvisor ⊣ IT Asset Recovery Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph,
 append-only audit ledger. An ITAD (IT Asset Disposition) operator
 coordination actor (device-intake data logging, data-wipe scheduling
 against an intake device, battery-hazard/unverified-sensitive-data
 concern flagging, resell/refurbish/certified-recycle disposition
 proposal against a device) -- not direct destruction-equipment-
 actuation authority and not R2v3-conformance/data-destruction-
 certification authority. Four ops (`:log-device-intake` /
 `:schedule-data-wipe` / `:flag-safety-concern` / `:propose-
 disposition`), all `:effect :propose` only. Thirteen concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct destruction-equipment control), permanent
 destruction-equipment-actuate block, permanent R2v3-conformance/
 data-destruction-certification-authority block, independent device
 verification/registration before EITHER wipe scheduling or
 disposition proposal (single-entity gate, documented departure from
 this fleet's usual two-entity shape -- see docs/adr/0001-
 architecture.md Decision 0), independent data-wipe-sufficiency
 recompute against NIST SP 800-88's own Clear/Purge/Destroy taxonomy
 for data-bearing dispositions (resell/refurbish require Purge or
 Destroy, never trusted on the advisor's self-report), double-schedule
 guard, double-disposition guard, disposition-value validation,
 category validation, functional-status validation, and wipe-level
 validation. Safety-concern flagging (battery-hazard/thermal-runaway/
 unverified-sensitive-data) ALWAYS escalates to a human ITAD
 coordinator; `:log-device-intake` is the only op eligible to
 auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
